HEADWORD: Phryganeides
<hw>Phryg`a*ne"i*des</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[NL.,
fr. <ets>Phryganea</ets>, the typical genus, fr. Gr. <?/ a dry
stick.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A tribe of neuropterous insects
which includes the caddice flies; -- called also
<altname>Trichoptera</altname>. See <er>Trichoptera</er>.</def>
<altsp>[Written also <asp>Phryganides</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

